article.headline: Cornell 74, Brown 65
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Adam Gore scored 18 points to lead Cornell to a 74-65 win over Brown in Ivy League basketball Saturday night. Geoff Reeves added 14 points, and Jeff Foote scored 13 points, grabbed eight rebounds and blocked two shots for Cornell (18-5, 10-0). Reeves made 5-of-5 field goals and scored on 4-of-4 three-point tries. Cornell shot 43.6 percent overall, scored on 11-of-22 shots from beyond the arc and made 15-of-17 free throws. Damon Huffman scored a game-high 19 points for Brown (15-9, 7-3), which had four players who scored in the double digits. Chris Skrelja was the only player in the game with a double-double, scoring 12 points and grabbing 11 rebounds. Mark McAndrew scored 18 points, while Matt Mullery added 10. Brown shot 46.3 percent for the game, was 8-of-22 on three-pointers and 19-of-26 from the foul line.
